headline: Looking At The Narrative For Centene (CNC) As Margin Hopes Meet Medicaid Risks
summary: Centene’s fair value estimate has shifted only slightly, from about US$39.94 to about US$41.12, but that small move sits on top of some meaningfully updated assumptions. The model now uses a marginally lower discount rate of roughly 7.25% instead of about 7.30%, and a modestly higher revenue growth assumption of around 4.88% versus about 4.66%, reflecting the tug of war between optimism around margin recovery and concern over Medicaid and contract risks seen in recent Street commentary.
